    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>butternut squash cubes</strong> to a heatproof bowl</p><p>Cover the bowl with <strong>cling film </strong>and pierce a few holes in the top</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until the squash is fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/brown-butter-and-crispy-sage-mafaldine-with-butternut-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large dry pan over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>pine nuts </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden</p><p>Once golden, transfer to a plate (save the pan!) \u2013 these are your <strong>toasted pine nuts</strong></p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/brown-butter-and-crispy-sage-mafaldine-with-butternut-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Return the reserved pan to a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>softened butternut squash </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until golden</p><p>Once golden, transfer to a plate, reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/brown-butter-and-crispy-sage-mafaldine-with-butternut-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the <strong>butternut</strong> is cooking, add your <strong>mafaldine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the mafaldine for 7-9 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the mafaldine, reserving 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml]</span> <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>reserved starchy pasta water </strong>with your <strong>clotted cream </strong>and <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>pasta stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/brown-butter-and-crispy-sage-mafaldine-with-butternut-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wipe the reserved pan clean and return it to a medium-heat</p><p>Once hot, add 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Swirl the butter around the pan as it melts, and cook for 3-5 min or until the butter starts to brown and smell nutty, then remove the pan from the heat \u2013 this is your <strong>brown butter</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/brown-butter-and-crispy-sage-mafaldine-with-butternut-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the butter browns, crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing it with the side of a knife and discard the skin</p><p>Strip your <strong>sage</strong> from their stems and discard the stems</p><p>Once the butter has browned, add the <strong>crushed garlic</strong> and <strong>sage</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until the garlic is fragrant and the sage is crisp</p><p>Transfer the <strong>crispy sage</strong> to the plate with the pine nuts and discard the <strong>garlic </strong>(save the pan!)</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/brown-butter-and-crispy-sage-mafaldine-with-butternut-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat, then add the <strong>drained pasta </strong>and <strong>pasta stock</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce coats the pasta</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> with a very generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>brown butter mafaldine</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/brown-butter-and-crispy-sage-mafaldine-with-butternut-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>brown butter mafaldine </strong>and crumble over the <strong>crispy sage</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>remaining Italian hard cheese </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>salad </strong>and <strong>browned butternut squash </strong>to the side and dress with your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong></p><p>Sprinkle the <strong>toasted pine nuts </strong>over the top</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
